      [Note:
      Apparently, there was a procedural lapse here; I have no record of a
      motion to amend.  However, it seems that no one complained that they did
      not know what they were voting on.  I have used different "bullets" in
      the motion above to indicate what I understand to be the accumulated
      effect of this free-for-all:
 
          --  means keep the bullet item this as is
          ++  means delete the reference to clause 5.9 from this bullet item
          xx  means delete this entire bullet item
      :DS]
 
